SIMPLE: positively
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Positively
<hw>Pos"i*tive*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In a positive manner;
absolutely; really; expressly; with certainty; indubitably;
peremptorily; dogmatically; -- opposed to
<xex>negatively</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Good and evil which is removed may be esteemed good or evil
comparatively, and <qex>positively</qex> simply.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Give me some breath, some little pause, my lord,⟦br⟧
Before I <qex>positively</qex> speak herein.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I would ask . . . whether . . . the divine law does not
<qex>positively</qex> require humility and meekness.</q>
<rj><qau>Sprat.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Positively charged</b></col> <it>or</it>
<col><b>Positively electrified</b></col></mcol> <fld>(Elec.)</fld>,
<cd>having a charge of positive electricity; -- opposed to
<ant>negatively charged</ant>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Positiveness</ent>⟦br⟧
